# E2E tests for Flight endpoints (VS Code REST Client)

### Get all flights (no filter)
GET http://localhost:8080/flights
Accept: application/json

### Get flights filtered by status (e.g., "SCHEDULED")
GET http://localhost:8080/flights?status=SCHEDULED
Accept: application/json

### Create a new flight (valid payload)
POST http://localhost:8080/flights
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "rocketId": "r1",
  "departureDate": "2025-12-01T10:00:00",
  "basePrice": 1500.0
}

### Create a flight with missing rocketId (error case)
POST http://localhost:8080/flights
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "departureDate": "2025-12-01T10:00:00",
  "basePrice": 1500.0
}

### Create a flight with invalid date format (error case)
POST http://localhost:8080/flights
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "rocketId": "r1",
  "departureDate": "invalid-date",
  "basePrice": 1500.0
}

### Create a flight with negative basePrice (error case)
POST http://localhost:8080/flights
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "rocketId": "r1",
  "departureDate": "2025-12-01T10:00:00",
  "basePrice": -100.0
}

### Create a flight with zero basePrice (error case)
POST http://localhost:8080/flights
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "rocketId": "r1",
  "departureDate": "2025-12-01T10:00:00",
  "basePrice": 0.0
}

### Create a flight with departureDate in the past (error case)
POST http://localhost:8080/flights
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "rocketId": "r1",
  "departureDate": "2020-01-01T10:00:00",
  "basePrice": 1500.0
}

### Create a flight with departureDate more than 1 year ahead (error case)
POST http://localhost:8080/flights
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "rocketId": "r1",
  "departureDate": "2027-12-01T10:00:00",
  "basePrice": 1500.0
}

### Create a flight with missing basePrice (error case)
POST http://localhost:8080/flights
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "rocketId": "r1",
  "departureDate": "2025-12-01T10:00:00"
}
